Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

IXU_TRANSCOSTTAX_COSTTRIKAMT)*/ SUM(C4.AMOUNT) AS C4_AMOUNT, SUM(C4.AMOUNTPC) AS C4_AMOUNTPC, SUM(C4.AMOUNTQC) AS C4_AMOUNTQC, SUM(C4.AMOUNTSC) AS C4_AMOUNTSC, C4.CURIK AS C4_CURIK, C4.TRANSIK AS TRANSLATIONSSUB WHERE TRANSLATIONSSUB.TRANSLATEIK = TRANSLATIONS.TRANSLATEIK AND TRANSLATIONSSUB.INSTR = C4_COSTS.COST AND C4.COSTIK = C4_COSTS.COSTIK AND C4_CUR.CURIK = C4.CURIK AND TRANSLATIONS.TRANSLATE = :v1 AND TRANSLATIONS.TRNSLUSE = :v2 AND (regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST4'||'(;|$)', 'i')) GROUP BY C4.CURIK, C4.TRANSIK, C4_CUR.CURIK, C4_CUR.CUR) COST4, (SELECT /*+ INDEX(TRANSCOSTTAX IXU_TRANSCOSTTAX_COSTTRIKAMT)*/ TRANSCOSTTAX.TRANSIK AS COST_ALL_TRANSIK, SUM(case when regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST1'||'(;|$)', 'i') then TRANSCOSTTAX.AMOUNTPC end) AS COST1_AMOUNTPC, SUM(case when regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST1'||'(;|$)', 'i') then TRANSCOSTTAX.AMOUNTQC end) AS COST1_AMOUNTQC, SUM(case when regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST1'||'(;|$)', 'i') then TRANSCOSTTAX.AMOUNTSC end) AS COST1_AMOUNTSC, SUM(case when regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST2'||'(;|$)', 'i') then TRANSCOSTTAX.AMOUNTPC end) AS COST2_AMOUNTPC, SUM(case when regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST2'||'(;|$)', 'i') then TRANSCOSTTAX.AMOUNTQC end) AS COST2_AMOUNTQC, SUM(case when regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST2'||'(;|$)', 'i') then TRANSCOSTTAX.AMOUNTSC end) AS COST2_AMOUNTSC, SUM(case when regexp_like(TRANSLATIONSSUB.OUTSTR, 'COST3'||'(;|$)', 'i') then TRANSCOSTTAX.AMOUNTPC end) AS COST3_AMOUNTPC, SUM(case when Undo Segment Summary

  • Min/Max TR (mins) - Min and Max Tuned Retention (minutes)
  • STO - Snapshot Too Old count, OOS - Out of Space count
  • Undo segment block stats:
  • uS - unexpired Stolen, uR - unexpired Released, uU - unexpired reUsed
  • eS - expired Stolen, eR - expired Released, eU - expired reUsed

  • Top SQL statements by DB Time along with the top events by DB Time for those SQLs.
  • % Activity is the percentage of DB Time due to the SQL.
  • % Event is the percentage of DB Time due to the event that the SQL is waiting on.
  • % Row Source is the percentage of DB Time due to the row source for the SQL waiting on the event.
  • Executions is the number of executions of the SQL that were sampled in ASH.

Top Blocking Sessions

  • Blocking session activity percentages are calculated with respect to waits on enqueues, latches and "buffer busy" only
  • '% Activity' represents the load on the database caused by a particular blocking session
  • '# Samples Active' shows the number of ASH samples in which the blocking session was found active.
  • 'XIDs' shows the number of distinct transaction IDs sampled in ASH when the blocking session was found active.

  • 'Slot Count' shows the number of ASH samples in that slot

  • '% Event' is 'Event Count' over all ASH samples in the analysis period
